The Greeks do not rightly use the terms ‘coming into being’ and ‘perishing'. For
nothing comes into being nor yet does anything perish, but there is mixture and
separation of things that are. So they would do right in calling the coming into
being ‘mixture', and the perishing ‘separation’.
